of projects, you know, bless those people because it was very painful. But they documented very well.

00:19:47.560 --> 00:19:52.520
OK, so they documented the internal work process of how to make the external technology

00:19:54.760 --> 00:20:01.079
work for us. So that's enterprise view. My role is really specifically in R&D.

00:20:01.880 --> 00:20:05.319
And in R&D, we have quite a different situation because

00:20:07.400 --> 00:20:11.640
it's research. Right. And so you have this research culture. And if you haven't worked

00:20:11.640 --> 00:20:19.079
in research, it may be hard to explain or my explanation may fall sort of one dimensional.

00:20:19.079 --> 00:20:26.599
But you never know what's going to happen. So you charter a project and it's very difficult

00:20:26.599 --> 00:20:33.400
to estimate the next things that you need because it could just totally fail and whatever. And so

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:43.160
that's the way R&D project reviews and and resourcing is used to. And then you're working

00:20:43.160 --> 00:20:53.160
with all these people from information systems who have project managers and they have, you know,

