00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:23.160
is called scale up. They know that it's hard and it doesn't work. And it requires all these specific

00:23:23.160 --> 00:23:28.760
types of engineer to make it happen. And so we're trying to say, this is the exact same, just because

00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:33.719
you've done it in your development environment. And this model works really good. There's still

00:23:33.719 --> 00:23:39.719
this whole process to get from that to a production software solution. And you can put

00:23:39.719 --> 00:23:44.680
up the architecture diagram and see, and be like, look, these are like pipes. Data has to flow

00:23:44.680 --> 00:23:50.760
