00:52:06.840 --> 00:52:11.719
use that tool that you taught me how to use or whatever it is. So how do you guys handle that,

00:52:11.719 --> 00:52:19.239
or is it not an issue for Dow? Sorry, million-dollar question.

00:52:20.120 --> 00:52:21.239
I'm letting Amanda go first.

00:52:24.199 --> 00:52:30.120
I mean, I've definitely seen it be an issue at Dow, like, when people go through, like,

00:52:30.120 --> 00:52:37.320
more generic Azure service training, and then we've Dow-ized the environment, so then they

00:52:37.320 --> 00:52:41.399
can't do things exactly how they learned in the training, so that can be really frustrating,

00:52:42.600 --> 00:52:47.320
and so, you know, we're still working through combating that, but I think, like, as far as

00:52:47.320 --> 00:52:52.199
getting, like, giving people access to other tools, I haven't seen so much. Like, people want to go do

00:52:52.199 --> 00:52:59.239
a jump training, cool, then they'll have access to Jump or Simca Pro or whatever it is, but I've

