definitely kind of raised those issues to leadership that could actually help us take action,

00:53:16.120 --> 00:53:22.439
you know? Like, we got leadership to help us talk to security about, like, the issues that were

00:53:22.439 --> 00:53:32.199
preventing people from having a similar experience. I know Alex, James, and I definitely

00:53:32.199 --> 00:53:39.959
were on many calls in the past about those kinds of things, and so I think we still leverage the

00:53:39.959 --> 00:53:47.159
Insight Scientist community to help us through that to try to make it as easy as possible for

00:53:47.159 --> 00:53:54.199
people to deliver their work while also still doing it in a secure manner. Yeah, I'm so glad

00:53:54.199 --> 00:53:58.760
you brought that up. That is another one of the key things that the Insight Scientist community

00:53:58.760 --> 00:54:06.120
does, is serve as a collective voice for, like, the technical people on the ground, right? Because

00:54:06.120 --> 00:54:14.439
you have, what you get is you have, you know, senior leaders that go talk to tech company

00:54:14.439 --> 00:54:21.000
executives and hear sales pitches and whatever, and it's like, this is so easy, you know, it'll

00:54:21.000 --> 00:54:28.199
accelerate your work, and then they bring them in and we do a training, and then it's like, okay,

00:54:28.199 --> 00:54:32.760
I'm committed to this training, I see all the content, we're working through it, it's good,

00:54:33.479 --> 00:54:40.360
and then we get it in the DAO environment and with the DAO security policies and work processes

00:54:40.439 --> 00:54:46.679
and all that stuff, and it's nothing like it was in the training, right? And then your senior

00:54:46.679 --> 00:54:51.959
leaders don't understand why, you know, they haven't seen the acceleration that they were told

00:54:51.959 --> 00:54:57.719
